summary: MY WIFE WAS DRIVING NORTH ON I-75 ABOUT 70MPH IN HER CADILLAC 2004 SRX. THE SUNROOF WAS COMPLETLEY OPENED AND BOTH FRONT PASSENGER WINDOWS WERE CLOSED AND BOTH REAR PASSENGER WINDOWS WERE OPEN. ALL OF A SUDDEN SHE FELT A POP IN HER EARS AND THEN THE REAR WINDOW SHEID SHATTERED.  THERE WAS NO OUTSIDE TRAUMA TO THE VEHICLE.  WE ARE WORRIED THAT THIS MIGHT BE A PRESSURE EQUALIZATION PROBLEM AND A DEFECT IN THE VEHICLE.  PE05-052.PCO
